- [ ] Creates new deployment record with `type: 'rollback'` and `source_deployment_id`
- [ ] Allocates a port from the production range
- [ ] Starts container from the target deployment's image
- [ ] Runs health check with 10 retries at 2s intervals
- [ ] Updates Caddy to route traffic to the new container
- [ ] Stops the current production container gracefully
- [ ] Releases the old port allocation
- [ ] Archives the previous production deployment
- [ ] Updates `projects.production_deployment_id` to the new rollback deployment
- [ ] On failure: marks new deployment as `failed` with error message
- [ ] Logs all steps with structured Pino logging

